    <summary type="html">&lt;h2 id=&quot;Capacity-and-Modulation&quot;&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;#Capacity-and-Modulation&quot; class=&quot;headerlink&quot; title=&quot;Capacity and Modulation&quot;&gt;&lt;/a&gt;Capacity and Modulation&lt;/h2&gt;&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Shannon Limit: Channel Capacity &amp;#x3D; B*log&lt;sub&gt;2&lt;/sub&gt;(1+S&amp;#x2F;N)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;B is Bandwidth, S is Signal strength, N is Noise.&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/br&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;&lt;p&gt;Amplitude Shift Keying(ASK): Represent number by different amplitude&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;It works well in wired networks because signal strength does not decrease much with distance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PAM-5: five level pulse amplitude modulation, used in 100BASE-T and 1000BASE-T Ethernet&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;PAM-16: used 10GBASE-T Ethernet</summary>
    
    
    
